Expression, Serializable
All Known Implementing Classes:
AndExpression, BindVariableAndExpression, BindVariableExpression, CompareEqualExpression, CompareExpression, ConstInstanceofExpression, ContainsExpression, ContainsKeyExpression, EmptyExpression, EndsWithExpression, EqualExpression, EqualTypeExpression, Extension, InExpression, InKeyExpression, InstanceofExpression, InSubQExpression, InValueExpression, IsEmptyExpression, IsNotEmptyExpression, MatchesExpression, NotContainsExpression, NotEqualExpression, NotEqualTypeExpression, NotExpression, OrExpression, StartsWithExpression, WhenCondition, WhenScalar
interface Exp
extends Expression

An Expression represents a query ready for execution. Generally, it is a set of conditions that must be met for the query to be true.

Author:

initialize

ExpState initialize(Select sel,
                    ExpContext ctx,

Initialize the expression. This method should recursively initialize any sub-expressions or values.

Parameters:
contains - map of relation paths to the number of times the paths appear in a contains() expression; used to ensure paths used for contains() within the same AND expression used different aliases
